<TITLE> Govt to 'comb out' Shibir </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 11 (bdnews24.com) The home ministry has ordered concerned agencies to comb out activists of Islami Chhatra Shibir from campuses across the country, Shamsul Haque Tuku, state minister for home affairs said Thursday as developments continued to unfold in the aftermath of the violence at Rajshahi University two days ago. Tuku told reporters after a meeting at the ministry that government agencies have been ordered to conduct operations to identify and uproot Shibir elements in all educational institutions. Home minister Sahara Khatun, Tuku and senior officials of all law enforcing agencies including the police attended the meeting. "Orders have been issued to comb all educational institutions infested with Shibir especially those in the northern districts of the country," said Tuku. The ruling Awami League's student wing Chhatra League has locked in deadly clashes with the Chhatra Shibir, student wing of the fundamentalist opposition ally, Jamaa-e-Islami Bangladesh. Chhatra League activist Faruk Hossain was killed on the night of Feb 8 at Rajshahi University by Shibir cadres who cut off tendons of his hands and feet and dumped him in a nearby sewer, said the police. The police launched a search operationg immediately following the news of this incident became public. The police then launched combing operations at Rajshahi University and adjacent villages where Shibir is said to have a strong base of supporters and cadres. In the wake of the RU clashes and killing, clashes have erupted at many places across the country between activists of Chhatra League and Chhatra Shibir. Tension prevails at Chittagong University also, which is regarded as another Shibir stronghold. bdne
